node.text:
@thedetour_duo know a thing or two about road trips, so we wanted to send them on a trip that gave them a little taste of everything Virginia has to offer. From oceanfront vibes and incredible thrills to historical treasures and Blue Ridge Mountain views (not to mention some other amazing stops along the way), follow along their journey that was iconically Virginia. 
A special thanks to all the businesses who helped make their vacation possible: @doctaylors @repeal_vb @jyfmuseums @jrarchaeology @greatwolflodge @casa_pearl @notanotherpancakehouse @buschgardensva @triplecrossing @casadelbarco @rubyscoopsic @graduatehotels @perlysrichmond @tjmonticello @michietavern @thelocalcatering

node.title: WanderLove: Iconic Virginia from Coast to Cliff

node.text: John Park knows a thing or two about great food, and "The Hungry Asian" @hungryasianrke founder wants to discover some of what Virginia has to offer - so he and his wife hit the road to explore the foodie scene in Fairfax, Virginia. node.text:
Located on the York River, Machicomoco is the newest state park in Virginia and the first to honor and celebrate the legacy of the Native Tribes of Virginia. The park's name is an Algonquian word that translates to "special meeting place," and is intended to be a space for education, reflection, and outdoor exploration. 🏕️ #VAoutdoors

📷 : @virginiaflair
